HEADWORD: cardiogram
<hw>car"di*o*gram`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kardi`a</grk> heart + <ets>-gram</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Any instrumental record made of heart
activity, especially the curve or tracing made by a cardiograph.
Sometimes used synonymously with
<altname>electrocardiogram</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cardiography</ent>⟦br⟧
